spanishExample: Puedes contar con él como siempre has contado.
englishTranslation: You can count on him like you have always counted.

spanishExample: Cuéntame qué pasó; eso no parece normal.
englishTranslation: Tell me what happened; that doesn’t seem normal.

spanishExample: No cuentes todo el peso.
englishTranslation: Don’t count all the weight.

spanishExample: No me contó todo lo que hizo ese día, así que ¡cuéntame!
englishTranslation: She didn’t tell me everything she did that day, so tell me!

spanishExample: Puedes tener la mayor parte de la sal.
englishTranslation: You can have most of the salt.

spanishExample: El oro está en el banco trasero.
englishTranslation: The gold is on the rear bench.

spanishExample: Contamos todo el efectivo que teníamos.
englishTranslation: We counted all the cash we had.

spanishExample: Las historias que cuentas no son siempre verdaderas.
englishTranslation: The stories you tell aren’t always genuine.

spanishExample: Si no cuentan toda la historia, yo la contaré.
englishTranslation: If they don’t tell the whole story, I will tell it.

spanishExample: No dejes que te cuente esas historias.
englishTranslation: Don’t let him tell you those stories.

spanishExample: La próxima vez quiere que le cuente la historia del rey y la reina.
englishTranslation: Next time he wants me to tell him the story about the king and the queen.

spanishExample: No tengo que contarle las noticias.
englishTranslation: I don’t have to tell him the news.

spanishExample: Estoy contando el dinero para poder darte el vuelto.
englishTranslation: I’m counting the money so I can give you the change.

spanishExample: Siempre cuento mis cosas.
englishTranslation: I always count my things.

spanishExample: Toma asiento y cuéntame una historia.
englishTranslation: Take a seat and tell me a story.

spanishExample: Había un traje en una caja en la basura.
englishTranslation: There was a suit in a box in the trash.

spanishExample: Cuéntale la historia que tuve que contarte.
englishTranslation: Tell her the story that I had to tell you.

spanishExample: Va a contarme una historia la próxima semana y la siguiente yo voy a contarla.
englishTranslation: She’s going to tell me a story next week and the following one I’m going to tell it.

spanishExample: Nunca me cuenta nada de lo que pasa en su vida.
englishTranslation: She never tells me anything of what happens in her life.

spanishExample: Puedes contar conmigo, ya te conté todo lo que sé.
englishTranslation: You can count on me, I already told you everything I know.

spanishExample: A su perra no le gusta el cambio.
englishTranslation: Her dog(f) doesn’t like change.

spanishExample: Cuente el dinero, por favor.
englishTranslation: (Formal) Count the money, please.

spanishExample: No quiere que cuentes otra vez, porque ya contaste.
englishTranslation: She doesn’t want you to count again, because you already counted.
